1 Section 4-120. A. The registration of any registered voter
2 shall be canceled only for one of the following reasons:
3 1. Written notice from the voter pursuant to Section 4-120.1 of
4 this title;
5 2. Death;
6 3. Conviction of a felony;
7 4. Judicial determination of mental incapacitation under Title
8 30 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
9 5. Registration in another county or state;
10 6. Failure to respond to a confirmation of address mailing and
11 failure to vote as prescribed in Section 4-120.2 of this title;
12 7. The surrendering of the voter’s Oklahoma driver license to
13 Service Oklahoma upon being issued a driver license in another
14 state; or
15 8. Being excused from jury duty for not being a citizen of the
16 United States; or
17 9. Determination that the voter is not a citizen of the United
18 States.
19 B. For purposes of this section, paragraphs 5 and 7 of
20 subsection A of this section shall constitute confirmation from the
21 voter to cancel his or her voter registration due to a change of
22 residence.
