1 C. A list of voter registrations that were canceled during the
2 previous twenty-four (24) months, and the reason for the
3 cancellation, shall be made available to the public.
4 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 4-122 of Title 26, unless there
6 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 A. The Secretary of the State Election Board may compare the
8 list of registered voters in this state with the database of any
9 federal, state, or local agency, board, or commission that maintains
10 information regarding the citizenship of persons residing in this
11 state.
12 B. If a registered voter definitively matches a person who is
13 recorded in a database described in subsection A of this section as
14 not being a citizen of the United States, the Secretary or his or
15 her designee shall send a notice of such finding to the voter. The
16 voter shall, within thirty (30) days from the date the notice is
17 sent to the voter, present proof of citizenship to the secretary of
18 the county election board in the county where the voter is
19 registered.
20 C. If a voter fails to present proof of citizenship within the
21 prescribed time to the county election board or otherwise provides
22 notice that the voter is not a citizen, then the voter’s
23 registration shall be canceled, and the voter shall be reported to
24 the appropriate district attorney and United States attorney.
