9 Section 7-103.2. A. 1. County election boards shall maintain
10 a current list of all registered voters in each precinct, which will
11 reflect the address and party affiliation of each voter. The list
12 shall be public information.
13 2. The list shall only be shared with a court system if that
14 court system agrees to regularly provide the names of persons
15 convicted of a felony in that court system to the Secretary of the
16 State Election Board and the appropriate secretary of a county
17 election board, or if the court system is required by state law to
18 provide such information.
19 3. The list shall note any voter for whom a first-class mailing
20 from the county election board or the State Election Board was
21 returned undeliverable.
22 B. 1. The Secretary of the State Election Board shall ensure
23 that an electronic copy of the voter registration list described in
